[00:57.77]	with Camillo to take away the life of our sovereign
[01:02.38]	lord the king, thy royal husband: the pretence
[01:06.44]	whereof being by circumstances partly laid open,
[01:10.73]	thou, Hermione, contrary to the faith and allegiance
[01:15.26]	of a true subject, didst counsel and aid them, for
[01:19.63]	their better safety, to fly away by night.
