[02:45.70]	'Tis a derivative from me to mine,
[02:48.80]	And only that I stand for. I appeal
[02:52.06]	To your own conscience, sir, before Polixenes
[02:56.03]	Came to your court, how I was in your grace,
[02:59.93]	How merited to be so; since he came,
[03:03.19]	With what encounter so uncurrent I
[03:06.45]	Have strain'd to appear thus: if one jot beyond
[03:10.66]	The bound of honour, or in act or will
